Ant is a task-based build system.
You define targets (like "compile", "package", "deploy"), and each target executes a series of tasks (like javac, jar, copy).
Itâ€™s similar to writing a Makefile in XML.

Ant does not assume any project structure or lifecycle â€” you must explicitly tell it what to do and in what order.

